small use of implode 
what implode do just convert an array into a string 
what explodo do also convert or turn on string a array 

define an array:
$dates=[
    'username'=>'vlass',
    'gender' =>'masculine',
    'age' =>'21',
    'completed'=>1
    ];
    
we can print with foreach 

foreach($dates as $date(remenber this will take value from dates array){
print "<p>$date</p>";
vlassmasculine211int(1) we have ths solution 


then we do with implode its more excelent 
$date= implode(' - ', $dates);
var_dump($date);

string(26) "vlass - masculine - 21 - 1" this is a result

so this is a pretty good 
even we can print like vlass , masculine , 21, 1
